cs.CR, cs.RO, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.CY

The paper discusses the security issues in the robotics industry and presents a tool for footprinting robots. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also focuses on the robotics industry, making cs.RO (Robotics) another likely category. The paper also mentions the need for good security practices, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering). The tool presented in the paper is aimed at identifying vestiges of different robots, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the need for a robot security community, which falls under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
